TCP - Allows for multiplexing (splitting data between multiple applications)
TCP/UDP segment format:
<--      32 bits       -->
Source port #. dest port #
other header fields
application data

TCP Connection distinguished by 4 values - source IP & port and dest IP & port
Web servers have different sockets for each connected client

UDP - everything on server goes through one socket
Connection only identified by source IP and dest IP

rdt_send() - data
udt_send() - packet
rdt_rcv() - packet
deliver_data() - data

positive acknowledgements (ACKs) or negative (NAKs)
